make a terrible mistake.

07:13.240 --> 07:15.754
l'm just waiting
for my toaster strudel to pop.

07:19.560 --> 07:21.357
There we go.

07:23.760 --> 07:24.749
You told on me.

07:24.960 --> 07:29.431
Hey, you wouldn't listen to reason,
so now you're gonna listen to Mom.

07:30.240 --> 07:34.631
Alan, sweetheart, you know,
l only want the best for you, right?

07:36.320 --> 07:38.151
l do.

07:39.920 --> 07:41.956
l do.

07:42.680 --> 07:45.990
Which is why when Judith threw
you out, l was there supporting you.

07:46.160 --> 07:48.958
-You had other options?
-Don't be naive.

07:49.120 --> 07:50.758
l could have sucked up to Judith. . .

07:50.920 --> 07:53.036
. . .in order to have more access
to my grandson.

07:53.200 --> 07:55.111
But no, l burned that bridge.

07:55.280 --> 07:58.238
l said horrible things to her
that l can never take back.

07:58.400 --> 08:01.551
Keep in mind, this is a woman who
worked the phrase ''mousy bitch'' . . .

08:01.720 --> 08:03.517
. . .into her wedding toast.

08:07.320 --> 08:11.029
So if you two reconcile,
l'll have to apologize to her.

08:11.200 --> 08:14.954
-So?
-l'd rather kill us all.

08:16.640 --> 08:19.359
Okay, moving on.

08:19.560 --> 08:21.676
Rose? Do you have something
you'd like to say?

08:21.840 --> 08:23.956
Yes, thank you.

08:24.320 --> 08:28.472
Alan, when l first met you,
l didn't care for you at all.

08:28.640 --> 08:31.200
You were a fussy, whiny control freak.

08:36.400 --> 08:37.628
Yes? And now?

08:39.280 --> 08:41.350
