08:59.320 --> 09:02.437
Alan, life is all about moving on.

09:02.600 --> 09:06.229
Now, in the animal kingdom,
sharks move forward. . .

09:06.400 --> 09:08.391
. . .while crabs move sideways.

09:08.560 --> 09:11.233
So the question you have to ask
yourself is:

09:11.400 --> 09:14.233
Are you a shark or a crab?

09:18.080 --> 09:19.593
Which way do Sea-Monkeys move?

09:22.400 --> 09:23.469
Okay, that's Judith.

09:23.640 --> 09:25.835
Now, l thank you for your concern. . .

09:26.000 --> 09:28.639
. . .but l would appreciate it
if nobody said anything. . .

09:28.800 --> 09:30.791
. . .and everybody just stayed out of it.

09:34.080 --> 09:35.433
Yeah, right.

09:36.320 --> 09:38.675
-Hey, Mom.
-Hi, honey. Why aren't you dressed?

09:38.840 --> 09:42.116
l told you l was picking him up early.
Why isn't he ready? Get dressed.

09:42.280 --> 09:43.872
-l'm sorry.
-You're always sorry. . .

09:44.040 --> 09:45.871
. . .but l always play the bad guy.

09:46.040 --> 09:48.429
-Damn it, Alan.
-Okay, he's gone.

09:48.600 --> 09:51.239
-l was thinking about you last night.
-Really?

09:51.400 --> 09:54.198
-What were you thinking?
-Just what a nice time l had.

09:54.360 --> 09:55.679
Yes, yes, it was.

10:01.840 --> 10:02.829
Alan?

10:11.920 --> 10:13.751
Turn around.

10:14.480 --> 10:15.799
Hi, Judith.

10:16.640 --> 10:18.471
Hello. How are you?

10:18.640 --> 10:19.675
Fine.

10:20.520 --> 10:22.033
Bye, Dad. Bye, everybody.

10:22.200 --> 10:23.633
Bye, Jake.

10:24.840 --> 10:27.752
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

10:30.400 --> 10:33.710
-Thanks for staying out of it.
-You're welcome.

10:37.240 --> 10:39.913
Hey, Alan. Come on out,
l got a surprise for you.

10:40.080 --> 10:43.152
Can it wait? Jake forgot
his math book. l'll run it to Judith's.

10:43.320 --> 10:45.151
No, no, no.
You can't go to Judith's.

10:45.320 --> 10:46.799
