-What?

13:20.400 --> 13:21.674
l'm thirsty.

13:21.840 --> 13:24.434
-Have something to drink.
-There's no more Goofy Juice.

13:24.600 --> 13:27.160
-So have some water.
-Fine.

13:30.520 --> 13:33.398
-Hey, Mom?
-What?

13:35.000 --> 13:37.195
l'm hungry too.
Can you make me a sandwich?

13:37.360 --> 13:40.557
-No. Have your drink and go to bed.
-Fine.

13:43.160 --> 13:44.957
Mom.

13:46.680 --> 13:49.274
-How about a cookie?
-You already brushed your teeth.

13:49.440 --> 13:51.112
-No, l didn't.
-You said you did.

13:51.280 --> 13:52.952
l always say that.

13:53.120 --> 13:56.635
-Well, then brush them and go to bed.
-Fine.

13:57.720 --> 13:59.551
Oh, God.

14:08.600 --> 14:09.635
Are you okay?

14:09.840 --> 14:13.071
There was a bright light
and l saw my dead grandma.

14:14.720 --> 14:16.711
She seemed happy.

14:16.920 --> 14:18.399
Here, have a little wine.

14:18.560 --> 14:20.835
Thank you. Thank you.

14:21.120 --> 14:22.155
That was close.

14:22.320 --> 14:23.992
Relax, he didn't see you.

14:24.200 --> 14:26.794
But what if he comes back?
Maybe l should go.

14:27.000 --> 14:29.719
Or we could go upstairs
and get in bed.

14:30.720 --> 14:32.153
Bed?

14:32.360 --> 14:34.237
-Our old bed?
-My new bed.

14:34.440 --> 14:36.670
Oh, what was wrong
with the old one?

14:36.840 --> 14:38.637
-Too many memories.
-Of what?

14:38.800 --> 14:41.268
You pretending to sleep
and me watching Letterman?

14:42.440 --> 14:44.351
Alan, do you wanna have this
conversation?

14:44.520 --> 14:47.751
No, l don't. But apparently,
my mouth has a mind of its own.

14:47.960 --> 14:49.837
Well, let's put your mouth
to better use.

14:50.600 --> 14:53.353
l can't go back underwater, Judith.

14:58.120 --> 15:00.076
-Hey, Charlie.
-Yeah?

15:00.240 --> 15:01.878
Not that it's any of my business. . .

15:02.040 --> 15:04.190
. . .l couldn't help noticing
the matched set. . .

15:04.360 --> 15:06.954
. . .of rotating floozies
on your deck earlier.

15:07.160 --> 15:10.118
They were for Alan. l was trying
to get his mind off of Judith.

15:10.280 --> 15:13.795
With a night of meaningless,
impersonal group sex?

15:13.960 --> 15:16.076
What a good brother.

15:16.680 --> 15:19.319
No, no, a good brother
gets him a couple of girls.

15:19.480 --> 15:22.916
lt takes a great brother
to get him two from the same egg.

15:24.560 --> 15:29.236
You know, there is a possibility
that we were wrong about this.

15:29.400 --> 15:31.630
Maybe Alan and Judith
can work things out.

15:31.840 --> 15:33.478
